FBIS3-3212 "drchi053_d_94008" FBIS-CHI-94-053 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Mar 1994 Northeast Asia DPRK Official in Geneva Denounces U.S. Talks Cancellation SK1803132694 Beijing China Radio International in Korean 1100 GMT 18 Mar 94 SK1803132694 Beijing China Radio International Language: Korean Article Type:BFN [Text] (Han Sang-u), deputy chief of the DPRK mission in the UN Headquarters in Geneva, yesterday denounced the United States for having unilaterally canceled the DPRK-U.S. high-level talks and hindered the thorough resolution of the nuclear issue on the Korean peninsula. (Han Sang-u) stated that the attitudes of the United States and the International Atomic Energy Agency [IAEA] had complicated this matter and that it was difficult to predict their consequences. On 16 March, the IAEA denounced Korea for having rejected the IAEA specialists' [words indistinct] inspection of nuclear facilities. Using this as an excuse, the United States later declared that it would cancel the 21 March DPRK-U.S. high-level talks. The ROK and the United States are reportedly holding negotiations on the Team Spirit joint military exercise.
